<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880310-0129 </DOCNO><HL> ITT to Buy Back More Shares </HL><SO> </SO><CO> ITT </CO><IN> BBK </IN><DATELINE> NEW YORK  </DATELINE><TEXT>   ITT Corp. directors authorized the buy-back of as many as five million common shares &quot;as market conditions warrant.&quot;    The company previously authorized the buy-back of as many as 10 million common shares, of which it has purchased 9.1 million. ITT has 150 million shares outstanding.    In composite trading on the New York Stock Exchange, ITT's common closed yesterday at $46.75 a share, up 12.5 cents.    The company's businesses include industrial products, insurance, financial services, hotels and natural resources. </TEXT></DOC>